 Saladdin Ahmed shows that capitalism imposes a totalitarian social mode of existence and neoliberalism perpetuates fascism as a class of ideology across nationalist and religious movements. This book, then, is both a theorization and an argument in favor of the application of the episteme of the silenced as the essence of the critical education necessary for achieving universal emancipation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical theory. 0aThéorie critique. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Critique. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849433340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438494333423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438494333/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles